HEADWORD: Imperiousness
<hw>Im*pe"ri*ous*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of
being imperious; arrogance; haughtiness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Imperiousness</qex> and severity is but an ill way of
treating men who have reason of their own to guide them.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imperishability</ent>⟦br⟧
